What I have learnt today:
In JavaScript, Math.floor() is a built-in Math object method that returns the largest integer less than or equal to a given number. 
It effectively rounds down a number to the nearest whole number (integer) that is less than or equal to the original number.
This help to avoid recurring numbers, instead of 3.333333333 it will be 3 

Example:
Math.floor(3.8);   // returns 4
Math.floor(7.2);   // returns 7
Math.floor(0);     // returns 0
Math.floor(5.5);  // returns 6
